snippet.textDisplay: Cool idea for a build vid guys / gals.  As a minor note - When explaining installed case fans, I don't recall you explaining the arrows for correct orientation.  For the nvme, I don't recall mentioning checking the manual to be sure you use the correct nvme slot (for example on my Crosshair hero vii, the slot furthest from cpu is used to run off cpu lanes).  And the 3 pin fan header on 4 pin header would depend on the motherboard and orientation but should only connect one way properly.  Keep up the great work!
snippet.textOriginal: Cool idea for a build vid guys / gals.  As a minor note - When explaining installed case fans, I don't recall you explaining the arrows for correct orientation. I'm amazed you pulled this off without a swiss army knife, tweezers, and only a thin line of thermal paste.

snippet.textDisplay:
The only things I found to add so far is connecting the SATA cables and the POST Test.

1. Many motherboards actually disable the SATA_0 or SATA_1 slot when you have a M.2 drive installed. Make sure you check the manual for any details of the aforementioned.
2. Checking to make sure your PC does POST before you put it in the case can save you a lot of headache.

Great video LTT.
